Mines produce raw materials for use by refineries.  Refineries convert the raw materials to refined materials, which are stored for use in the construction of new units.  The first and second monitors from the left above the GID indicate the numbers of raw and refined materials points currently available to us.  Although refineries depend on mines for materials, our mines and refineries need not be located on the same systems.  Refineries will draw from any available Empire-controlled mine.  Optimally, however, we should have at least one refinery for each mine - maintaining this balance generates maintenance points, and allows the production cycle to function more efficiently.